    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Armchairs designed to be the largest pieces of furniture in a sitting room, particularly common in 17th-century Britain and America. They are made of wood, usually with conspicuous carvings and occasionally with upholstered seats. They may resemble a throne.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
